Money Stuff =0A Every so often around here, I feel compelled to mention my =
all-time favorite =0AUS Securities and Exchange Commission enforcement acti=
on, the M =0A=0A=0A <> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click=3Fs=3D825881=
&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D11773803&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233be620525&p=3D1120=
2024>=0A=0A=0A=0AOverstock=0A=0AEvery so often around here, I feel compelle=
d to mention my all-time favorite =0AUS Securities and Exchange Commission =
enforcement action, theMAAX zips case <> =0Aagainst hedge fund manager Phil=
 Falcone and his firm Harbinger Capital =0APartners. In 2006, Harbingerowne=
d some bonds <>, called =E2=80=9Czips,=E2=80=9D issued by MAAX =0AHoldings =
Inc., a =E2=80=9Cleading manufacturer and distributor of bathtubs and showe=
rs =0Ain Canada.=E2=80=9D The bonds were distressed =E2=80=94 MAAX eventual=
ly went bankrupt in 2008 =E2=80=94 =0Aand Harbinger started buying them at =
around 50 cents on the dollar.=0A=0ABut in the summer of 2006, the Harbinge=
