ey, so they don=E2=80=99t need to disclose much to anyone. This is not =0As=
trictly true of Jane Street, though: It hasissued bonds <>, so its financia=
ls =0Aarenow somewhat public <>. Still, if you want an answer to the questi=
on =E2=80=9Chow =0Amuch do the top people at Jane Street get paid,=E2=80=9D=
 a trade-secrets lawsuit is =0Aprobably your best chance. Though not good e=
nough.=0A=0A=0AThings happen=0A=0AArchegos=E2=80=99 Hwang <> Faces Sentence=
 for Crimes That Shook Wall Street. Credit =0ASuisse <> =E2=80=9Chad an alm=
ost perfect risk culture for a disaster like the Great =0AFinancial Crisis.=
=E2=80=9D Antitrust Enforcers Prepare Final Blitz AgainstBig Tech <>. =0ATr=
afiguraCuts Share Buybacks <> as New Generation Takes Over. Bitcoin <> Rise=
s =0Ato Record With MicroStrategy Stepping Up Purchases. Italy puts brakes =
on=0A=E2=80=98reckless=E2=80=99 e-scooter use <> with new helmet and insura=
nce rules. Jersey Mike=E2=80=99s =0AFounder <> Is Worth $7 Billion After Bl=
ackstone Deal. Here=E2=80=99s Steve Schwarzman =0Aeating a Jersey Mike=E2=
=80=99s sub <>. Dental supply stock surges on RFK=E2=80=99s =0Aanti-fluorid=
e stance <>, activist involvement.=0A=0AIf you'd like to get Money Stuff in=
 handy email form, right in your inbox, =0Apleasesubscribe at this link <>.=
 Or you can subscribe to Money Stuff and other =0Agreat Bloomberg newslette=
rshere <>. Thanks!=0A=0A=0A <> =0A=0A=0A[1] That=E2=80=99s from the SEC com=
plaint. I would not have said =E2=80=9Ccover=E2=80=9D: Whoever was =0Ashort=
ing the zips was borrowing notes =E2=80=94 perhaps Falcone=E2=80=99s =E2=80=
=94 to *do* the short, =0Abut =E2=80=9Ccover=E2=80=9D normally means buying=
 back the bonds to close out the short.=0A=0A[2] Sometimes we talk about co=
mpanies where short interest is more than 100% =0Aof the outstanding shares=
, whichpeople incorrectly believe <> means that there =0Amust be naked shor=
t selling. It does not. That said, the Harbinger complaint =0Agoes on: =E2=
=80=9CHarbinger was able to acquire more than the entire issue of the MAAX =
=0Azips because there is no =E2=80=98locate=E2=80=99 requirement when short=
-selling debt =0Ainstruments. Under rules applicable to the equities market=
, a broker or dealer =0Athat is not engaged in bona fide market making cann=
ot accept a short sale order =0Ain a stock unless it has borrowed or has ar=
ranged to borrow that stock, or has =0Areasonable grounds to believe that i=
t can borrow the stock and deliver on the =0Adelivery date. There is no sim=
ilar rule applicable to bond trading. Thus, =0A=E2=80=98naked=E2=80=99 shor=
t selling of bonds is legal, which can lead to =E2=80=98long=E2=80=99 posit=
ions far =0Ain excess of the issue size.=E2=80=9D In principle Harbinger co=
uld acquire more than =0A100% of the bonds without any naked shorting, but =
in that case *it would =0Aprobably have to lend out its bonds*. Here it see=
ms like Harbinger called in =0Aits bonds that were being loaned out, and co=
uld keep buying new bonds from =0Ashort sellers, because those short seller=
s really were (legally) naked short.=0A=0A[3] The SEC complaint sort of hal=
fheartedly alleges that he deceived people by =0Anot telling everyone that =
he owned all the bonds earlier, but he=E2=80=99s not actually =0Aobligated =
to do that, and there=E2=80=99s no suggestion that he affirmatively lied.=
=0A=0A[4] Or borrows it and maintains a short position in both the parent a=
nd the =0Aspinoff. But ultimately, when she closes out her short, the short=
 seller has to =0Adeliver both shares.=0A=0A[5] The MMTLP case is weird bec=
ause the SEC accuses the company *both* of =0Aengineering this sort of shor=
t squeeze *and* of pretending to engineer this =0Asort of short squeeze to =
trick retail investors and pump its stock. Or, rather, =0Aone or the other,=
 but the SEC isn=E2=80=99t sure which. There is an argument that the =0Afir=
st theory is legal, if short squeezes are legal, and the second theory is =
=0Anot (it=E2=80=99s fraud).=0A=0A[6] Now called Beyond Inc <>., after acqu=
